text: Hessen Cassel is an unincorporated community in Marion Township, Allen County, in the U.S. state of Indiana. ==History== Hessen Cassel was platted in 1863. Hessen Cassel was originally built up chiefly by Germans, and was named for the Landgraviate of Hesse-Kassel in Germany. ==Geography== Hessen Cassel is located at . ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Allen County, Indiana Category:Unincorporated communities in Indiana Category:Fort Wayne, IN Metropolitan Statistical Area
